Halve the @sugar snap peas{80%grams}.

Trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the
length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(peeled), or use a #garlic press{}.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%grams} and season with
@salt{} and @pepper{}.

Fry until golden brown on the outside and cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its
> packaging. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the chicken browns, bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with
@salt{1/4%tsp}.

When boiling, add the @egg noodle nest{125%grams} to the water and cook until
tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and run under cold water to stop them sticking
together.

Once the chicken has browned, add the sugar snaps, @red Thai style paste{50%grams}
and garlic to the pan.

Stir-fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Add the cooked noodles, carrot ribbons, @ketjap manis{50%grams},
@sugar{1/2%tsp for the sauce} and @water{50%milliliter for the sauce} to the pan.
Stir together until well combined and piping hot, then remove from the heat.

Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Share the Thai inspired chicken noodles between your #bowls{}.

Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%grams} to finish. Enjoy!

> Step 2 MOD: If you've chosen chicken breast instead of thigh, cook in the same
> way.